text.__SUMMARY__:
Chamaelaucium marchantii is a member of the family Myrtaceae endemic to Western Australia.The dense, rounded and many branched shrub typically grows to a height of 1 to 1.8 metres (3 to 6 ft). It blooms in October producing yellow-green flowers.Found along creeks and on breakaway slopes in a small area in the Mid West region of Western Australia near Northampton where it grows in sandy soils.
